</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_janolaw">1. Janolaw</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong><a href="http://www.janolaw.de/agb-service/#menu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Janolaw</a></strong> is a platform for German legal issues that can provide you with current legal documents for your online store. Along with providing legal services relating to <strong>terms and conditions</strong> as well as providing support for your <strong>privacy policy</strong>, Janolaw also offers further important documents for your shop, such as <strong>cancellation rights</strong> and a <strong>legal disclosure</strong>. These documents can be ordered with or without an update service. There are different service packages available from Janolaw, which you can order on the Janolaw website.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_signing_up_for_janolaw">2. Signing up for Janolaw</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Sign up at <strong>Janolaw</strong> and order the service pack that meets your needs. You will receive the <strong>access data</strong> that you need for setting up the interface in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_setting_up_janolaw_in_plentymarkets">3. Setting up Janolaw in plentymarkets</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to set up <strong>Janolaw</strong> in your plentymarkets system, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up Janolaw:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Client (store) » Standard » Services » Janolaw</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pay attention to the explanations given in table 1 and carry out the <strong>settings</strong> as desired.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
