</div></div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Table 2: <strong>Janolaw</strong>; template variables for the <strong>online store</strong></em></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_e_mail_templates">4.2. E-mail templates</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Insert the template variables into the corresponding section of your <strong>e-mail template</strong>. Template variables that have the extension <strong>Text</strong> need to be entered into the corresponding <strong>Text</strong> tab. Similarly, ones that have an <strong>HTML</strong> extension need to be entered into the <strong>HTML</strong> tab.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the following <strong>template variables</strong> to integrate the data into your <strong>e-mail templates</strong>:</p>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<colgroup>
